\"from\": 640, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the discus\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 669}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic record\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"his winning throw\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2004 Athens Games\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mykolas Alekna took this collegiate season off to prepare for the Olympics, and he got the full attention of the track and field world when he unleashed a throw of 243-11 (74.35 meters) on April 13 at Ramona, Okla. That eclipsed the 38-year-old world record of 243-0 (74.08) set by East Germany\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Jurgen Schult in 1986 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 16 years before Alekna was born.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 765, \"end\": 779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mykolas Alekna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramona\", \"score\": 0.9664192863278971, \"rank\": 0.03474756158846151, \"text\": \"Ramona\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ramona\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this collegiate season\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"the full attention\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"the track and field world\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"a throw\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"243-11 (74.35 meters\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"the 38-year-old world record\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"East Germany\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Jurgen Schult\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"1986 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 16 years\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"Alekna\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alekna is the choice of Track and Field News, Sports Illustrated and USA Today to win gold at Paris, although Athletics Weekly gave the nod to 2022 world champion Kristjan Ceh of Slovenia.\\u00c2 The only other automatic qualifiers to the finals out of the first group were Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Matthew Denny (219-3/66.83) and Austria\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lukas Weisshaidinger (218-11/66.72).\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1218, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996136462705, \"rank\": 3.8635399723913165e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Weekly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\"}, {\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Denny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Denny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Denny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Denny\"}, {\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lukas_Wei\\u00dfhaidinger\", \"score\": 0.9999994854589618, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lukas Weisshaidinger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lukas_Wei\\u00dfhaidinger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lukas_Wei\\u00dfhaidinger\"}], \"noun_phra